e.%20%26quot%3BDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20doctors%20couldn't%20see%20patients%20as%20regularly%20and%20non-emergency%20procedures%20were%20postponed%2C%20so%20there's%20a%20backlog%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENiren%2C%20who%20has%20lived%20in%20both%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%2C%20voiced%20similar%20concerns.%20He%20said%20his%20own%20mother%2C%20who%20needs%20a%20hip%20replacement%2C%20was%20on%20a%20waitlist%20for%2018%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20people%20who%20have%20to%20fly%20to%20other%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%94%20to%20get%20cancer%20treatment%20because%20it%20takes%20too%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20US%2C%20you%20can%20get%20a%20specialist%20appointment%20in%20two%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENiren%20also%20said%20Canadians%20paid%20elevated%20taxes%20to%20support%20such%20a%20comprehensive%20healthcare%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20call%20it%20free%20healthcare%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20free%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20expensive%20because%20you're%20paying%20through%20the%20taxes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228af511bd-4cef-4447-96f8-e2383dcbf3f4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20American%20found%20relief%20from%20the%20US's%20violence%20and%20opioid%20crises%20in%20Canada%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Ouellet%2C%2040%2C%20left%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20for%20Victoria%2C%20British%20Columbia%2C%20in%202020.%20It%20wasn't%20his%20first-choice%20destination%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20he%20ended%20up%20finding%20the%20peace%20and%20safety%20he%20was%20looking%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20his%20partner%20had%20planned%20to%20move%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-moving-to-new-zealand-california-nature-quality-of-life-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWellington%2C%20New%20Zealand%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20were%20unable%20to%20because%20of%20pandemic%20border%20lockdowns.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20characteristics%20Ouellet%20was%20looking%20for%20in%20New%20Zealand%2C%20he%20said%2C%20he%20found%20in%20British%20Columbia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20love%20the%20Pacific%20Northwest%2C%20and%20Canada%20is%20not%20far%20up%20the%20road%2C%26quot%3B%20Ouellet%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20similar%20weather%2C%20and%20they%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20things%20that%20we%20wanted%20and%20what%20we%20were%20looking%20for%20in%20New%20Zealand%2C%20which%20was%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20education%2C%20socialized%20healthcare%2C%20and%20politics%20that%20weren't%20so%20incredibly%20polarizing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOuellet%2C%20who%20works%20for%20the%20provincial%20government%20at%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20in%20British%20Columbia%2C%20spoke%20glowingly%20of%20Portland%20but%20did%20point%20out%20the%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20bad%26quot%3B%20violence%20and%20opioid%20crises%20he%20witnessed%20in%20the%20US%20overall.%20Before%20Portland%2C%20he%20and%20his%20partner%20lived%20in%20Chicago.%20The%20violence%20they%20would%20read%20about%20or%20see%20on%20their%20daily%20commutes%20prompted%20them%20to%20move%20west%20and%20eventually%20out%20of%20the%20country%20altogether%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20hasn't%20had%20the%20same%20worries%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20British%20Columbia%2C%20the%20regulations%20for%20being%20able%20to%20own%20a%20gun%20are%20extremely%20tight%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20out%20in%20public%2C%20and%20you%20hear%20a%20noise%2C%20no%20one%20runs%2C%20no%20one%20checks%20over%20their%20shoulder%2C%20no%20one%20thinks%20that%20it%20could%20possibly%20be%20gun%20violence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20there%20was%20still%20an%20opioid%20crisis%20in%20British%20Columbia%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20as%20striking%20as%20it%20is%20in%20Portland.%20Ouellet%20said%20that%20in%20the%20three%20years